Package: kdeborder
Title: Kernel density estimation correcting for border bias
Version: 0.1.0
Author: Arthur Charpentier and Ewen Gallic
Maintainer: Ewen Gallic <ewen.gallic@gmail.com>
Description: This package proposes some R codes to compute the kernel density estimates of two-dimensional data points, 
    using an extension of Ripley's circumference method to correct for border bias.
License: GPL-3
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
Depends: rgdal, surveillance, maptools, ggplot2, ellipse, fields, ks, maps, rgeos, parallel, sp, ggmap, reshape2, grDevices, methods
RoxygenNote: 6.0.1
